Mnemonic

Target IP: 10.10.196.107

Scanning



There are three TCP ports open on the target machine: FTP, HTTP, and SSH.

Enumeration

Port 80: HTTP

The empty webpage above is displayed for this port application. The source-code does not hint anything either.


I found a zip file using feroxbuster with the command feroxbuster -u http://10.10.196.107/ -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirbuster/directory-list-2.3-medium.txt -x zip -d 3.


I downloaded the zip file on my computer. It is password-protected so I cannot extract the files. I used john to obtain the hash and crack the password, as shown above. I extracted the file note.txt.


The note.txt contains the message above. I obtained the username ftpuser for FTP. Maybe I can bruteforce the password for this user?


And bingo! The user's password is love4ever. So I have the credential ftpuser:love4ever.


The FTP directory data-4 contains the files above. It contains two files: id_rsa and not.txt


Is there a new user called james? Does the id_rsa belong to james?


I changed the permission of the key, and used john to obtain the passphrase which is bluelove.

Exploitation


Using the command ssh -i id_rsa james@10.10.196.107 -p 1337, I now have access to the SSH application as james. I now have a foothold on the machine.
